    {
      "id": "ex-li-1",
      "type": "listen",
      "skill": "listening",
      "prompt": "Listen to the speech opener. What does the speaker spotlight?",
      "audio": "audio/b2.2/unit-04-mise-en-relief/listen-1.mp3",
      "transcript": "Ce qui nous rassemble ce soir, c'est une conviction ; ce dont nous avons besoin, c'est de courage.",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "a",
          "text": "A shared conviction — and the need for courage"
        },
        {
          "id": "b",
          "text": "A new tax law and its budget"
        },
        {
          "id": "c",
          "text": "The size of the audience"
        }
      ],
      "correct": [
        "a"
      ],
      "explanation": "Two spotlights in a row: ce qui… c'est une conviction / ce dont… c'est de courage."
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-rd-1",
      "type": "read",
      "skill": "reading",
      "prompt": "Read the press review of a speech and answer both questions.",
      "passageFr": "Hier soir, l'ancienne députée a pris position contre la réforme. « C'est notre propre avenir que l'on brade », a-t-elle lancé, interpellant un public déjà conquis. Un seul regret pour cette oratrice : que son pauvre micro, défaillant dès la dixième minute, ait transformé la fin du discours en mime.",
      "passageEn": "Last night, the former MP took a stand against the reform. \"It is our own future being sold off,\" she declared, challenging an already-won-over audience. A single regret for this orator: that her poor (unfortunate) microphone, failing from the tenth minute, turned the end of the speech into mime.",
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "q1",
          "prompt": "« L'ancienne députée » means…",
          "options": [
            {
              "id": "a",
              "text": "The former MP"
            },
            {
              "id": "b",
              "text": "The very old MP"
            },
            {
              "id": "c",
              "text": "The MP for antiques"
            }
          ],
          "correct": [
            "a"
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "q2",
          "prompt": "« Son pauvre micro » — why does pauvre come BEFORE the noun?",
          "options": [
            {
              "id": "a",
              "text": "It means 'unfortunate', the figurative sense"
            },
            {
              "id": "b",
              "text": "It means the microphone was cheap"
            },
            {
              "id": "c",
              "text": "It's a printing error"
            }
          ],
          "correct": [
            "a"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-mc-4",
      "type": "multiple-choice",
      "skill": "writing",
      "prompt": "\"My own room\" =",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "a",
          "text": "ma propre chambre"
        },
        {
          "id": "b",
          "text": "ma chambre propre"
        },
        {
          "id": "c",
          "text": "ma chambre à propre"
        }
      ],
      "correct": [
        "a"
      ],
      "explanation": "Before the noun, propre = own; after, it means clean."
    },
